Russian President Vladimir Putin signed a law on the introduction of administrative responsibility for violation of the term and procedure for payment of goods (works, services) when making purchases for state and municipal needs.
This law is intended to solve a very acute problem of non-fulfillment of their obligations by customers in the implementation of state and municipal procurement.
Two years ago, the situation when entrepreneurs could not receive payment under already executed state and municipal contracts was widespread.
At the same time, the President of Russia instructed the Prosecutor General’s Office of the Russian Federation to take the problem under special control.
Because the businessmen themselves could not cope with unscrupulous customers who concluded contracts not backed by financing, tried in every possible way to evade the obligations to pay and included illegal conditions in the contracts.
The problem was systemic in the country as a whole.
Since 2015, in the interests of protecting the rights of entrepreneurs to receive payment on public orders, the prosecutor's office has made 9.7 thousand. According to the results of their consideration, 4.5 thousand were brought to disciplinary responsibility. Officials, to administrative - 533, 75 materials are submitted to the investigative bodies for the organization of procedural checks, 46 of them criminalized cases.
As a result, the debt to entrepreneurs in the amount of more than 66 billion rubles was repaid.
And these huge sums accumulated far from the result of non-payment of multibillion-dollar contracts.
Numerous, systematic delays in payment of services to entrepreneurs in far more modest debts have been brought to fabulous debts.
Here's a characteristic case.
The head of a small company won the competition for the provision of social transportation services for several million rubles.
The person invested all his working capital, fully fulfilled the obligations, but the money was not received on time.
The result is an increasing financial account of the debts on wages, taxes, loans that would lead to bankruptcy if the entrepreneur had not applied for help from the prosecutor’s office.
Now in a number of regions the problem has been mitigated as much as possible.
Nevertheless, as of the first half of 2017, the total amount of debt under state and municipal contracts, identified by prosecutors of the constituent entities of the Russian Federation, amounted to about 27.4 billion rubles.
In regions where debt indicators continue to reach critical values, the prosecutor’s office operates in the mode of manual anti-crisis management.
The Attorney-General personally holds visiting meetings with representatives of the local authorities, on which all violations revealed by prosecutors and measures to eliminate them immediately are met.
Such operational meetings this year have already been held in Yaroslavl and Yekaterinburg.
Qualitatively improve the payment discipline of public customers will be able to implement Federal Law No. 189-FZ "On Amendments to the Code of the Russian Federation on Administrative Offenses in terms of establishing the administrative responsibility of the officials of the customer for violation of the term and procedure for payment of goods (works, services) in the implementation of purchases to provide state and municipal needs", which was signed by the President of Russia last week.
The draft law was developed by the Ministry of Economic Development of Russia on the initiative of the Prosecutor General’s Office.
The new law will supplement the Code of the Russian Federation on Administrative Offenses with an article that provides for a fine of 30 thousand. up to 50 thousand. rubles for violation by the official of the customer of the term and procedure for payment of goods, works and services in state and municipal procurement.
And if the official has already been subjected to administrative punishment for a similar offense, then he will be disqualified for a period of one to two years.
All prosecutors of the constituent entities of the Russian Federation have already been instructed to ensure the application of these legislative novels in practice.
Civil Rights Protection Unit Announces Warning of Movement to Missouri
The National Association for the Advancement of Colored People issued a warning to colored people travelling to Missouri because of the state’s discriminatory policies and racist attacks.
The group’s statement reads: “The warning to travelers to the National Association to promote the progress of the colored population, valid until August 28, 2017, calls on African-American travelers, guests and citizens of Missouri to be especially careful and to exercise increased caution when traveling around the state due to a number of dubious racist incidents that have recently taken place throughout the state and brought here.”
According to the National Association for the Advancement of Colored People, to declare a travel warning prompted a recent law in Missouri, which made it harder for people to win discrimination-related lawsuits, and that state law enforcement agencies disproportionately choose their own targets of minorities.
“People are subject to human rights violations.
They are stopped on the roads because of the color of their skin, beaten and killed,” said Rod Chapel, president of the National Association for the Advancement of Colored People of Missouri.
“We hear complaints often than ever before.”
This is the first warning of its kind, announced by an organization in relation to the US state.
The group cited incidents such as the humiliation of black students on a racial basis at the University of Missouri and the death of twenty-eighth-year-old Tory Sanders, a black man from Tennessee.
Sanders died in suspicious circumstances earlier this year after he ran out of gasoline during a state trip, and Missouri police arrested him without being charged with the crime.
The warning also mentions a recent report by the Office of the State Attorney General of Missouri, according to which the probability of being stopped on the road for black drivers is 75 percent higher than for whites.
“The purpose of the warning is for people to be aware of the situation and warn their relatives and friends and colleagues about what might happen in Missouri,” Chapel said.
“People should be prepared in one way or another whether they will take money for the pledge or to inform relatives that they are traveling through the territory of the state.”
According to the latest data of the FBI’s hate crime report, 100 hate crimes were registered in Missouri in 2015, making the state the state sixteenth in the number of such violations.
Also, the travel warning is a response to the new Missouri law, after which it will be more difficult to initiate proceedings against a legal entity in connection with housing or labor discrimination.
Earlier, the American Civil Liberties Union (ACLU) announced warnings to travelers to Texas and Arizona after these states passed new immigration controls, according to which local law enforcement agencies were ordered to arrest people for violating immigration laws, which, according to ACLU, was supposed to increase the number of racial checks.
