Anorotali is a city as remote as abandoned; the road here includes an hour and a half flight from Jayapura, the administrative center of the province, in Nabira, and then a five-hour shaking on a hired car.
There is no public transport here.
The city with a population of about 19 000 people consists of wooden houses, enslaved by bamboo fences; roofs made of corrugated steel are painted with rust in various reddish shades.
Few people of Indonesians have come here, let alone journalists, and almost none of the foreigners.
Before the arrival of Christian missionaries, the papuas meme pago worshiped a god named Uga Tame.
There were other changes.
