But almost nothing has changed in Papua, and the locals feel betrayed.
“Our hearts are broken because in 2014 we voted for Jokovy, expecting him to fulfill our hopes for justice,” says Yoo.
In fact, just two months after the October inauguration, Jocovi Paniai survived the tragedy.
On December 7, 2014, a group of 11 children was on the street and sang Christmas hymns at the campfire in Enarotal as two Indonesian soldiers on a motorcycle escaped from the darkness.
