On May 19, the deputies adopted it in the first reading.
Last week, the State Duma Committee on State Construction and Legislation approved the text of the bill for the second reading, but now it has been redesigned again.
Now it says that the procedure for taking the oath will be established by the President of the Russian Federation.
Earlier, the parliamentarians were going to describe the procedure directly in the law “On citizenship of the Russian Federation”, indicating that the ceremony should take place in a solemn atmosphere in front of the state coat of arms and flag of Russia in the presence of a representative of the Ministry of Internal Affairs.
However, from the text of the bill it was not clear where such an event should be held - the list of places where it is possible to place the coat of arms of the Russian Federation is regulated by the relevant federal constitutional law.
These include courts, offices of heads of state authorities of subjects, municipalities, judges, prosecutors, heads of federal executive bodies, etc.
Most likely, it could be the registry office.
To make a solemn oath wishing to obtain Russian citizenship will be after officials check their documents.
But a Russian passport a person will receive only after taking the oath, follows from the revised text.
A week ago, the draft said that the oath should precede the signing of the decree.
The updated text says that Russia will swear to swear by Russia from the age of 18, and not with 14.
There is a rule by which incapacitated or limitedly capable or also those who cannot pronounce, read or personally sign the text of the oath will be freed from taking the oath.
In addition, the President of the Russian Federation has the right to release from this procedure and other persons,
Also, the updated bill prescribes a special procedure for the admission of residents of Ukraine to Russian citizens who are considered native speakers of the Russian language.
They will have to officially renounce Ukrainian citizenship, providing a corresponding application to the authorized body of Ukraine.
A notarized copy of the application will need to be transferred to Russian officials.
Refusal of “alien” citizenship, as it is now, is not required if it is provided for by an international treaty or if it is not possible “for reasons beyond the control of the person”.
The corresponding amendment to the law was proposed by a group of deputies, including First Vice-Speaker of the State Duma Ivan Melnikov (CPRF), Natalia Poklonskaya, Pavel Krasheninnikov and Airat Farrakhov (all - United Russia).
I think many of you know that it is simply impossible to get a certificate from Ukraine.
Accordingly, a lot of people are waiting for a decision on their fate on the citizenship of the Russian Federation, - explained the day before the head of the Duma Committee on state construction and legislation Pavel Krasheninnikov (EP).
In addition, the text clarified that restrictions on the occupation of certain positions for foreigners will not apply to those who renounced the “other” citizenship in writing and handed over the previous passport to the Ministry of Internal Affairs of Russia, but “for reasons beyond his control” he was not permanently considered a citizen of another country.
Now foreigners are prohibited from holding positions in the municipal service, to be hired for objects and in the organizations whose activities are related to ensuring the security of Russia.
Also, a person with dual citizenship or a residence permit of another country can not become a deputy of the State Duma or a member of the Federation Council.
It is planned that the law should enter into force on September 1, 2017, by that time the necessary by-laws should be ready.
