Judges are offered to protect against the chairmen
The Presidential Council for Human Rights (HRC) on behalf of Vladimir Putin has developed proposals to strengthen the independence of the judicial branch of government.
The HRC proposes to limit the powers of the chairmen of the courts and introduce their election.
For the courts of appeal and cassation instances, the HRC wants to introduce special districts that will not be tied to administrative-territorial division in the Russian Federation.
The Supreme Court should also submit its proposals under the presidential order.
The HRC has completed the development of proposals that will strengthen the independence of Russian justice.
This work was carried out by the HRC on behalf of Vladimir Putin of January 3, 2017, which the president gave after a meeting with members of the council.
At a meeting with members of the council on December 8, 2016, including individual cases of judicial arbitrariness, as well as problems of public control in places of detention of citizens were discussed. "K" from December 9).
The result of the work of the HRC was 25 proposals, which relate both to ensuring the independence of judges and identifying judicial errors, and financing of courts and legal education.
One of the ideas of the Kremlin human rights defenders is to limit the powers of the presidents of the courts to increase the independence of the remaining judges.
If the candidate for the position of judge successfully passed the competition and received the support of the judicial community, then the chairman of the court, in the opinion of the HRC, should submit him to its appointment, without having the right to refuse, as the law allows now.
It is also proposed to deprive the President of the right to distribute cases to judges.
To do this, experts allow, can be a specially written computer program.
