Now all the chairmen of the courts (from the republican to district) are appointed for six years by the president on the proposal of the Chairman of the Supreme Court of the Russian Federation.
To protect judges from the pressure of regional administrations, the HRC proposes to organize an appeal and cassation in courts of general jurisdiction in a new way.
Now their structure is tied to administrative-territorial division in the Russian Federation.
The HRC said that "it is necessary to ensure the organization of individual courts of appeal and cassation instances not at the level of regional judicial bodies in the constituent entities of the Russian Federation, but in judicial districts."
Experts take as a basis the practice of arbitration courts.
They have “judicial districts” that do not coincide with the administrative division in the Russian Federation, but guaranteeing at this expense a greater independence from regional officials who find it difficult to use “telephone law”.
The HRC proposes to strengthen the world judges of the HRC to consider some “categories of civil and administrative cases” with their participation.
For example, the deprivation of parental rights, on reinstatement, the protection of honor and dignity, deprivation of a driver's license, etc. p.
"These are only our proposals," explained Kommersant a member of the HRC, a retired Constitutional Court judge Tamara Morshchakova.
She also recalled that the President’s instructions applied not only to the HRC, but also to the Supreme Court (SC), which has not yet disclosed its proposals.
There is still time for the execution of the order of the Supreme Court (among the co-executors - the Prosecutor General's Office and the Commissioner for Human Rights in the Russian Federation).
