“We will be able to assess all the charges made now, only after we collect all the information and will be able to assess the situation.”
The Italian authorities are monitoring the ship Juventa, owned by Jugend Rettet, since October.
His crew is suspected of taking on board migrants who were sent directly to them by lifeboats and allowed smugglers to leave with the boats, which they could use again.
