The Russian authorities have recently significantly intensified their policy on the Libyan direction, and with visits to Moscow, delegations of the opposing Libyan sides have tacited.
The head of the Russian contact group on the intra-Libyan settlement under the Ministry of Foreign Affairs of the Russian Federation and the State Duma, the assistant to the head of the Chechen Republic Lev Devov told Kommersant what goals Moscow pursues in this region and who is betting on.
The contact group on Libya, which you head, is almost unknown.
Here, say, the contact group in Ukraine - everyone knows about it.
And here is the veil of secrecy.
What exactly do you do, what goals do you pursue?
The contact group was created at the initiative of the Ministry of Foreign Affairs of the Russian Federation and the State Duma.
Its activities are supervised by Deputy Foreign Minister Mikhail Bogdanov and Adam Delimkhanov (Deputy of the Duma from Chechnya. - "B"."
The latter is authorized to work in the Libyan direction by the speaker of the state Duma Vyacheslav Volodin.
