We managed to establish contacts with representatives of all major groups opposing each other in the Libyan conflict - and from Tripoli (where the UN-recognized government is based on Faiz Sarraj. - "Kommersant"), and with Tobruk (the residence of the parliament, which opposes the government and supports Marshal Khalifa Haftar, who controls the eastern regions of Libya. - "B"."
Thanks to the active participation of Ahmed Metig (Deputy Prime Minister of Libya - "Kommersant"), we quickly managed to agree on the release of Russian sailors.
Then it was decided to make more effective use of these contacts, to create a contact group.
Its task is to analyze the situation, identify key factors and players, dialogue with all parties to the conflict.
I want to emphasize that in Libya we do not want to be associated with any of the parties to the conflict, we are in dialogue with everyone.
How many people are in the contact group and how many of them are permanently in Libya?
Now the contact group includes five people.
Among them there are people who have experience in law enforcement agencies, including the Ministry of Defense.
We also want to introduce a group of specialists in the region, representatives of the Institute of the Middle East of the Russian Academy of Sciences.
No one is constantly in Libya, no one is in our staff, so far there is no need.
Are there any Russian military advisers in Libya, instructors?
And if so, whose side is it?
There are no Russian military specialists in Libya.
All conversations and publications are not true.
But your contact group is the former military...
Yes, and their presence is necessary.
For example, when we visit hot spots.
Or such cities closed for us for us as Misrata (where militia units are based, which played a role in the overthrow of Libyan leader Muammar Gaddafi in 2011 and noticeably intensified in subsequent years. - "B"."
We arrived in Misrata in January of this year.
We were frightened, they said that there are all Islamists, terrorists.
But it was important for us to assess the situation there ourselves, to analyze the real military potential, who is responsible for what, why there are such rumors, what is really the role of the Islamists.
In Misrata, we met with all representatives of the detachments that were engaged in the destruction of ISIS in Sirte (in December 2016, this city on the Mediterranean coast was recaptured from the militants of the Islamic State banned in Russia - Kommersant).
