This coated dinosaur coated with a powerful shell used red-and-white camouflage to hide from predators, and used a protective technique known as a protective color, which is also used by many animals of our days.
This would allow him to merge faster with the environment and avoid meeting with enemies, experts say, suggesting that he was hunted by larger dinosaurs.
