Electricity is cheaper for residents, and for producers of Buryatia
The efforts of the Soviet and post-Soviet authorities of the Republic of Buryatia (Eastern Siberia), which lasted more than a decade, to establish fair tariffs for consumers of electricity are beginning to bear fruit.
From September 1, the cost of low voltage electricity for industrial recipients has been reduced by 25%.
Federal Antimonopoly Service of the country in accordance with the Decree of the Government of the Russian Federation "On Amendments to the Rules of the Wholesale Market of Electricity and Capacity and the Consolidated Forecast Balance of Production and Supply of Electricity (Power) within the Unified Energy System of Russia for the Subjects of the Russian Federation" (from 17.07.2017. No. 842) set indicative electricity prices and capacity for industrial consumers of the Republic of Buryatia.
As a result, the cost of electric energy for Buryat producers is reduced by a quarter, which will greatly facilitate the lives of small and medium-sized enterprises and individual entrepreneurs.
For many decades, the leaders of the republic have beaten the thresholds of the Moscow offices in vain attempts to equalize the region in tariffs with a neighboring Irkutsk region with a cascade of hydroelectric power plants on the Angara, flowing from Lake Baikal, the main catchment area for which is Buryatia.
And only this year the progress began.
In March, tariffs for electric energy for the population of the republic were reduced from 4.24 rubles / kWh to 3.93 rubles / kWh, or by 7.3%.
With the inclusion of Buryatia by the decision of the federal government in the List of territories of the price zones of the wholesale market, for which the functions of the wholesale and retail markets are established, are the turn of industrial consumers.
According to analysts, this is only the beginning, since the population of the Irkutsk region pays 1.01 rubles for kilowatt/hour.
But no one dares to name at least the approximate date of the new tariff movement towards the downward of Buryatia.
