In Russia, there will be two new territories of advanced socio-economic development - "Abaza" and "Novotroitsk".
The relevant decrees of the Government of the Russian Federation will enter into force today, August 4.
The boundaries and types of economic activity of the TOR in the territory of the city of Abaza in the Republic of Khakassia are determined.
In the city, where 15 thousand people live, there will be a special legal regime of entrepreneurial activity, as well as a minimum amount of capital investments of residents, a minimum number of new permanent jobs.
It is assumed that this will attract about 2.5 billion rubles of investments to the city, and more than 600 new jobs will be created.
The list of types of economic activities, in which the TOR "Abaza" will operate a special legal regime of entrepreneurial activity, for example, includes crop production, livestock, food production, soft drinks and clothing.
Already, the Government of the Republic has signed framework agreements on the implementation of 8 investment projects.
It is also planned to reduce the dependence of the territory on the city-forming enterprise LLC "Abakansky mine".
In January 2017, the authorities of the region reported that Khakassia fulfilled all the conditions of the Ministry of Economic Development for the creation of TS.
The authorities of the Orenburg region did the same.
There, in the city of Novotroitsk, a territory of advanced socio-economic development will also be created.
This will diversify the economy of the single-industry city, reduce its dependence on the city-forming enterprise JSC "Ural steel", as well as create more than 2.3 thousand jobs and attract investments in the amount of more than 8 billion rubles.
The list of types of economic activities in which the new TOP will have a special legal regime for entrepreneurs includes, in particular, freshwater fish farming, the production of feed, medicines and medical materials.
Novotroitsk became the first of the monotowns of the Orenburg region to receive the status of TOR.
Recall that the territory of advanced development is an economic zone with preferential tax conditions, simplified administrative procedures and other privileges that is created to attract investment and improve the lives of the population.
Among the benefits for residents of the TOR can be distinguished the following: income tax in the amount of not more than 5% during the first five years, and at least 10% over the next 5 years, social contributions in the amount of 7.6% for 10 years, the use of the free customs zone regime, preferential mode of connection to various infrastructure facilities, as well as preferential rates on rent.
